  <title>IC - 49</title>
  <lyrics>[V0]
 US - 205
 FR - 120
 DE - 57
 PL - 205 
 RO

[V1]
 1. O happy they who know the Lord,
 1. Mon Dieu, Toi, Source de mes joies,
 1. O Jesu Nam’, du klingst so süß
 1. Szczęśliwy ten, kto Pana zna,
 1. Fericiţi cari ştiu pe Domnul,

[V2]
 With whom he deigns to dwell;
 De ce qui me ravit,
 In jedes Gläub’gen Ohr!
 Kto poznał Prawdy blask;
 Căci cu ei locuind,

[V3]
 He feeds and cheers them with his Word,
 Gloire de mes jours et mes voies,
 Du ziehst uns hin zu seinen Füß’
 Bo temu Pan nagrodę da,
 Îi hrăneşte-nveseleşte,

[V4]
 His arm supports them well.
 Et ma paix dans la nuit.
 Und hebst das Herz empor!
 Nie szczędząc ducha łask.
 Şi-i apără tare.

[V5]
 2. To them in each distressing hour,
 2. Si Tu parais quand tout se voile,
 2. Verwund’te Herzen heilest du,
 2. Kto Pana zna, ten w każdy czas
 2. În orice timp de necaz, au

[V6]
 His throne of grace is near;
 Mon aurore s’étend.
 Bist jedes Müden Kraft,
 Uniknie chwili złej;
 Tron de har aproape;

[V7]
 And when they plead his love and pow’r,
 Du matin Tu es mon étoile,
 Du gibst den Schwerbelad’nen Ruh
 Bo Pan obiecał bronić nas
 Şi când ei cer ajutorul,

[V8]
 He stands engaged to hear.
 Et mon soleil levant.
 Und Mut zur Ritterschaft.
 I mieć w opiece swej.
 Gata-I să-i asculte.

[V9]
 3. His presence sweetens all our cares,
 3. Les cieux ouverts pour moi rayonnent,
 3. Mein sich’rer Fels in wilder Flut,
 3. Obecność Pańska słodzi nam
 3. Prezenţa-I griji îndulceşte,

[V10]
 And makes our burdens light;
 Bonheur félicité;
 Mein Heil und Bergungsort!
 Cierpienia, znój i trud.
 Poveri uşurează;

[V11]
 A word from him dispels our fears,
 Toutes tes promesses résonnent,
 Mein Schutz bei grauser Stürme Wut,
 Kto Pana zna, ten widzi sam,
 Un cuvânt doar şi fug temeri,

[V12]
 And gilds the gloom of night
 Mon coeur veux Te louer.
 Mein letzter Ruheport!
 Jak szczęśliw Pański lud.
 Şi-aureşte tristeţi.

[V13]
 4. Lord, we expect to suffer here,
 4. Je veux suivre la route étroite,
 4. Mein Herr und König, Freund und Hirt,
 4. Kto Pana zna, ten szczęśliw jest,
 4. Doamne-aşteptăm suferinţe,

[V14]
 Nor would we once repine;
 Sur les pas du Seigneur,
 Mein Priester und Prophet,
 Bo kocha go też Pan.
 Nicicând nu ne-om plânge;

[V15]
 But give us still to find thee near,
 Courant sur le sol avec joie,
 Mein Weg und Ziel, wenn ich verirrt,
 A komu Pan dał ducha chrzest,
 Fă să Te simţim aproape,

[V16]
 And keep us wholly thine.
 Ta Parole en mon cœur.
 Mein Heil, sei hoch erhöht!
 Ten pozna Boski plan.
 Şi păstrează-ne-ai Tăi.</lyrics>
